        "text": "Piped with pipes",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".—The Greek Version has “danced in dances,” by a slight variation of reading. The graphic description of the acclamation of the people indicates something more than conventional loyalty. The attempt of Adonijah relied on the support only of the great men, and perhaps the army, but had no popular following.",
